Test file: src/claim-office.spec.ts
Implementation file: src/claim-office.ts
Failing test: "should apply 20% loyalty discount for customers with 2 or more years"
Expected behavior: Sword for a 2-year customer → premium 95 (100 base + 10 first ins - 20 loyalty + 5 fee)
Current error: expected 115 to be 95 — customer.years is ignored

The loyalty discount is a policy-wide modifier: -20% of the items premium (policy base premium) when customer has ≥2 years.

Current processScenario:
```typescript
export function processScenario(scenario: Scenario): ScenarioOutput {
  const results = scenario.steps.map((step) => {
    const itemsPremium = calculateItemsPremium(step.items);
    const premium = itemsPremium + itemsPremium * FIRST_INSURANCE_SURCHARGE_RATE + PROCESSING_FEE;
    return { premium };
  });
  return { results };
}
```

Need to add: if customer.years >= 2, subtract 20% of itemsPremium from the premium.

Modified line:
```
let premium = itemsPremium + itemsPremium * FIRST_INSURANCE_SURCHARGE_RATE;
if (scenario.customer.years >= 2) {
  premium -= itemsPremium * 0.2;
}
premium += PROCESSING_FEE;
```

Note: The Scenario interface has `customer: { years: number }`. The test input uses `yearsWithMHPCO` or `years` — check the existing test conventions. Previous tests use `{ customer: { years: 0 } }`.

All 12 existing tests use `years: 0`, so adding the loyalty discount only for years >= 2 won't affect them.

EXPERIMENT MODE: Run autonomously, proceed to Refactor after completion.

